      <hedline>
        <hl1>How Big a Role on a Global Stage?; The Allies and the U.N.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard May letter on importance of UN; notes that experience of last century is that US cannot go it alone (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''America in the World'' (editorial, Aug. 7) made little reference to  allies of the United States and none to the United Nations.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''America in the World'' (editorial, Aug. 7) made little reference to  allies of the United States and none to the United Nations.</p>
        <p>Although we are a ''military and economic colossus,'' the experience of the last century is that we cannot go it alone.</p>
        <p>RICHARD MAY  Nyack, N.Y., Aug. 7, 2000</p>
      </block>
